race.comment: FRISKEE FROG (4) didn't finish it off on soft going at the Sapphire Coast but brought a string of near-misses to that. His nose defeat three back in a Goulburn CL1 was the best of them and the speedy galloper draws low. Kissick replaces the 3kg apprentice and he's well placed to win. LYSANDER (2) led and missed a half length here over 1400m and then pulled up with an issue at Bathurst following beaten 2.3L in a 58 at this trip. He's been freshened at Owen is a positive jockey booking. Rates to be in the finish. INCANTATA (12) presents third-up for the in-form Olive yard and is on a quick back-up. The gate is awkward, but she carries just 53kg and can make the finish. KOTAISHI (1) should give this a shake.
